    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n  <title>Integration Testing Demo</title>\n  <style>\n    body {\n      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n      margin: 2em;\n      background: #f9f9f9;\n      color: #333;\n    }\n    h1 {\n      color: #2c3e50;\n    }\n    section {\n      background: #fff;\n      padding: 1em 1.5em;\n      border-radius: 6px;\n      box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\n      margin-bottom: 2em;\n    }\n    pre {\n      background: #eee;\n      padding: 1em;\n      border-radius: 4px;\n      overflow: auto;\n    }\n    button {\n      background: #2980b9;\n      color: white;\n      border: none;\n      padding: 0.5em 1em;\n      font-size: 1em;\n      border-radius: 4px;\n      cursor: pointer;\n    }\n    button:disabled {\n      background: #95a5a6;\n      cursor: not-allowed;\n    }\n    .test-result {\n      margin-top: 1em;\n      font-family: monospace;\n      white-space: pre-wrap;\n    }\n    .pass {\n      color: green;\n    }\n    .fail {\n      color: red;\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Integration Testing Demo</h1>\n  <section>\n    <h2>Concept Explanation</h2>\n    <p>\n      <strong>Integration Testing</strong> is a testing level where individual units or modules \n      are combined and tested as a group. The purpose is to validate the interaction and data flow \n      between modules to detect interface defects and ensure they work together correctly.\n    </p>\n    <p>Unlike unit tests (testing components in isolation), integration tests focus on combined behavior.</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Example Modules</h2>\n    <p>We have three simple modules simulating user registration flow:</p>\n    <ol>\n      <li><code>validateUserInput</code> – Validates user data (unit-level).</li>\n      <li><code>saveUserToDB</code> – Simulates saving to a database (mocked).</li>\n      <li><code>sendWelcomeEmail</code> – Simulates sending an email.</li>\n    </ol>\n    <p>The integrated <code>registerUser</code> function calls all three to complete registration.</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Integration Test</h2>\n    <p>Click the button below to run the integration test. The test checks if all modules cooperate correctly:</p>\n    <button id=\"runTestBtn\">Run Integration Test</button>\n    <div id=\"testResults\" class=\"test-result\"></div>\n  </section>\n\n  <script>\n    // Module 1: Validate user input\n    function validateUserInput(user) {\n      if (!user) return false;\n      if (typeof user.name !== 'string' || user.name.trim() === '') return false;\n      if (typeof user.email !== 'string' || !user.email.includes('@')) return false;\n      return true;\n    }\n\n    // Module 2: Save user to \"database\" (simulated async)\n    function saveUserToDB(user) {\n      return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n        // Simulate some async DB latency\n        setTimeout(() => {\n          // Mock: Reject if email is already registered (hardcoded)\n          if (user.email === 'already@taken.com') {\n            reject(new Error('Email already registered'));\n          } else {\n            resolve({ id: 101, ...user });\n          }\n        }, 100);\n      });\n    }\n\n    // Module 3: Send welcome email (simulated async)\n    function sendWelcomeEmail(user) {\n      return new Promise((resolve) => {\n        // Simulate latency sending email\n        setTimeout(() => {\n          resolve(`Email sent to ${user.email}`);\n        }, 50);\n      });\n    }\n\n    // Integration function: Register User\n    async function registerUser(user) {\n      if (!validateUserInput(user)) {\n        throw new Error('Invalid user data');\n      }\n      const savedUser = await saveUserToDB(user);\n      const emailResponse = await sendWelcomeEmail(savedUser);\n      return {\n        user: savedUser,\n        emailResponse,\n      };\n    }\n\n    // Simple assertion helpers\n    function assert(condition, message) {\n      if (!condition) throw new Error(message);\n    }\n\n    // Integration test function\n    async function integrationTest() {\n      const results = [];\n      \n      // Test case 1: Successful registration\n      try {\n        const user = { name: 'Alice', email: 'alice@example.com' };\n        const response = await registerUser(user);\n\n        assert(response.user.id === 101, 'User ID should be set to 101');\n        assert(response.user.name === 'Alice', 'User name should be Alice');\n        assert(response.emailResponse === 'Email sent to alice@example.com', 'Email response should match');\n        results.push({ test: 'Successful registration', status: 'PASS' });\n      } catch (e) {\n        results.push({ test: 'Successful registration', status: 'FAIL', error: e.message });\n      }\n\n      // Test case 2: Registration fails due to invalid email\n      try {\n        const user = { name: 'Bob', email: 'bob_at_example.com' };\n        await registerUser(user);\n        results.push({ test: 'Registration with invalid email should fail', status: 'FAIL', error: 'Expected error not thrown' });\n      } catch(e) {\n        results.push({ test: 'Registration with invalid email should fail', status: 'PASS' });\n      }\n\n      // Test case 3: Registration fails due to email already taken\n      try {\n        const user = { name: 'Charlie', email: 'already@taken.com' };\n        await registerUser(user);\n        results.push({ test: 'Registration with taken email should fail', status: 'FAIL', error: 'Expected error not thrown' });\n      } catch(e) {\n        results.push({ test: 'Registration with taken email should fail', status: 'PASS' });\n      }\n\n      return results;\n    }\n\n    // UI hook\n    document.getElementById('runTestBtn').addEventListener('click', async function() {\n      this.disabled = true;\n      const resultDiv = document.getElementById('testResults');\n      resultDiv.textContent = \"Running integration tests...\";\n      try {\n        const results = await integrationTest();\n        resultDiv.innerHTML = results.map(r => {\n          const colorClass = r.status === 'PASS' ? 'pass' : 'fail';\n          const errorMsg = r.error ? '\\nError: ' + r.error : '';\n          return `<strong class=\"${colorClass}\">${r.status}:</strong> ${r.test}${errorMsg}`;\n        }).join('\\n\\n');\n      } catch(e) {\n        resultDiv.innerHTML = `<span class=\"fail\">Test run failed: ${e.message}</span>`;\n      } finally {\n        this.disabled = false;\n      }\n    });\n  </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
